Responses.NAM1 - Response Text: Is the way clear of Redoran?
Do you want me to wait here?
Perhaps some day, yes. For example, I would greatly wish to see the Ashlands and their peoples with my own eyes.
But at present, my duties to the Morag Tong do not permit me to travel.
Will you travel together with me to Jobasha's Rare Books?
We leave the door to the Foreign Quarter Waistworks, turn right, west, continue down the hall and across the atrium on the same level,
then follow the opposite corridor west on the other side of the atrium all the way to Jobasha's door.
Will you travel together with me to Jobasha's Rare Books? We leave the door to the Foreign Quarter Waistworks, turn right, west,
continue down the hall and across the atrium on the same level, then follow the opposite corridor west on the other side of the atrium all the way
to Jobasha's door.
I must warn you: unless these troublesome fools are persuaded to behave like civilized beings, there may be fighting and killing if we try to travel
together.
Are we ready to travel together to Zainab camp? Do not worry if we must cross water, for I am an excellent swimmer.
But take care to protect me from wild beasts and bandits, for I have not learned any of the arts of war.
I do know a few spells, but they the spells of a household slave, and will probably be of little use if we are in danger. So. Shall we go now?
Are you ready now for me to accompany you to Zainab camp?
We travel together to Zainab camp. When we arrive there, we will speak further about my new bridegroom. Do you wish me to continue accompanying you?
It was quite a journey, wasn't it?
I am already safe and sound here at the shrine, but thank you for your concern.
We should resume our travels?
J'Saddha is safe now. J'Saddha thanks you.
Thank you for rescuing me. I will take a ship back to Ald'ruhn. I am sure my father, Miner Arobar, will reward you.
Thank you. I have duties I must attend to, and then I must find a way to reach my father. Until then, please deliver my locket to my father, Arethan Mandas.
Shall we continue on?
Shall we continue on? I must get to freedom.
Yes, I must find my beloved Sason.
Lead me where you will.
Should I continue to follow you to the Fields of Kummu?
Perhaps, but not today. I must travel with Sterdecan until he passes me on to another. If all goes well, I will see my homeland again.
I'm staying here until Frald the White says it's safe.
Do you want me to follow you?
No, but thank you. I will rest here and continue my pilgrimage when I can.
I can find my own way back to Gnaar Mok. It's not a long swim once I've had a chance to rest a bit.
Not right now, I have alot of work to do here. But thanks for getting me out of that tomb.
Do you want me to wait here?
Shall we travel together to Remasa Othril? She must still be here in Odirniran.
Thank you, but I can make my own way from here.
Not right now, I need to sell my goods here in Pelagiad. Thanks to you, everyone will know the name Tarvyn Faren as a trader who can reach his customers even with all the troubles for House Hlaalu.
Sorry, but I must stay here in Sarethi Manor until I am feeling better.
Do you want me to follow you to the Koal Cave?
Do you want me to wait here?
Thank you for helping me in my pilgrimage to the Koal Cave. I will stay here awhile and travel back to Ald'ruhn with another pilgrim.
Thank you for taking me to the Elf-Skerring. I was keeping these scrolls just in case something unfortunate happened.
Since I have arrived safely, I feel you deserve them.

Responses.NAM1 - Response Text: Now I can return to Summerset Isle. I've had enough of these Telvanni.
I have no interest in seeing the rest of Vvardenfell, but I appreciate your offer.
Do you want me to stay with you? I'd be willing to wait here. I m-mean, it's up to you.
We should continue to travel together, should we not?
It is best if I remain here.
You want that we keep going together? Probably a good idea.
I better stay here.
Do you want me to wait here?
Do you want me to follow you?
Do you want me to wait here?
Do you want me to follow you?
Do you want me to wait here?
Shall we travel back to my father, Athyn Sarethi?
Do you want me to wait here?
Are you ready to guide me back to Novor Drethan?
Do you want me to wait here?
Can you guide me back outside?
Should I keep following you to the Halfway Tavern in Pelagiad?
Do you want me to wait here?
Shall we travel together to Remasa Othril?
Do you want me to wait here?
Can we travel together to Maar Gan?
Do you want me to wait here?
Do you want me to follow you back outside this cave?
Do you want me to wait here?
Do you want me to follow you?
Do you want me to follow you? Abassel will try and kill me if I leave.
Do you want me to wait here?
Do you want me to follow you back to Ebonheart?
Do you want me to wait here?
Shall I follow you now?
Do you want me to wait here?
Shall we try and escape?
We must get to the Telvanni docks. Only then will I feel safe.
Yes, get me out of here. My father, Miner Arobar, will reward you.
Are there slavehunters near? Should J'Saddha wait?
If slavehunters are there, they see J'Saddha and kill J'Saddha. You sure you want J'Saddha to follow you?
Yes, we travel to the Mabrigash camp.
Do you want me to wait here?
Will you escort me back to the Imperial Cult Shrine at Fort Frostmoth?
